UAObjectType.Description: The CNC MotorType describes the key attributes necessary to describe a CNC Motor.

The CNC ChannelType describes the key attributes necessary to describe a CNC Channel. It provides the position information of the channel's tool center point in each coordinate system, and organizes the list of Axes and Spindles administered by a given Channel. An instance or extension of types in the CNC Base Profile may define as many instances of ChannelType as necessary to represent the specific CNC Machine.

The CNC AxisType describes the key attributes necessary to describe a CNC Axis. An instance or extension of types in the CNC Base Profile may define as many instances of AxisType as necessary to represent the specific CNC Machine.

The CNC SpindleType describes the key attributes necessary to describe a CNC Spindle. An instance or extension of types in the CNC Base Profile may define as many instances of SpindleType as necessary to represent the specific CNC Machine.

The CNC PositionType describes the key attributes necessary to describe position. It includes a Type property to describe the type of position described (ex: Linear, Rotational, Specific Coordinate Axis, etc.)
This base CNC type aggregates the key components of a CNC Machines. The types of each object are defined in the SM Profile http://cesmii.net/profiles/CNC.

The CNC MachineInformationType aggregates a set of key informational components of CNC Machines including its Coolant System, Identification, Status, and list of Tools. The types of each composition are defined in http://cesmii.net/profiles/CNC.
The CNC IdentificationType implements the Interface IMachineVendorNameplateType with additional CNC specific attributes.
The CNC MachineStatusType describes the key attributes necessary to describe a CNC Motor's Status.
The abstract Interface IToolInformationType specifies a set of attributes implemented by the Object or ObjectType where it is applied to.

The CNC ToolType aggregates a set of key CNC Tool components including Identification, Status, Information, and Tool Number. The types of each composition are defined in http://cesmii.net/profiles/CNC.
The CNC ToolStatusType describes the key attributes necessary to describe a CNC Tool's Status.
The CNC CommandType describes the key attributes necessary to describe commanded and actual values.
The CNC CoolantSystemType describes the key attributes necessary to describe a CNC Coolant System.
The abstract Interface ICoolantTankType specifies a set of attributes implemented by the Object or ObjectType where it is applied to.
The abstract Interface ICoolantPumpType specifies a set of attributes implemented by the Object or ObjectType where it is applied to.
The abstract Interface ICoolantFilterType specifies a set of attributes implemented by the Object or ObjectType where it is applied to.

UAVariable.Description: A globally unique resource identifier provided by the manufacturer of the machine
A human-readable, localized name of the manufacturer of the MachineryItem.

A string containing a unique production number of the manufacturer of the MachineryItem. The global uniqueness of the serial number is only given in the context of the manufacturer, and potentially the model. The value shall not change during the life-cycle of the MachineryItem.
